        <div id="gospel" class="pt-120 pb-0">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-12">
                        <div class="section-title text-center mb-60">
                            <h6>Gospel</h6>
                            <h2>Where Is Your Hope? </h2>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-xl-6 col-lg-6">
                        <div class="about-img mb-30">
                            <img src="/images/gospel.png" alt="gospel_tract_illustration">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-xl-6 col-lg-6">
                        <div class="faq__content mb-50">
                            <div class="accordion" id="accordionFaq">
                                <div class="accordion-item">
                                    <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingOne">
                                        <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button"
                                            data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseOne"
                                            aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseOne">
                                            Are you ready?
                                        </button>
                                    </h2>
                                    <div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse show"
                                        aria-labelledby="headingOne" data-bs-parent="#accordionFaq">
                                        <div class="accordion-body">
                                            <p>
                                                It is appointed that man must die and after that the judgment (Heb
                                                9:27). Are you ready to stand before the judgement seat of Christ?
                                            </p>
                                            <p>Jesus warned us that it will not profit us anything if we gain the whole
                                                world and lose our souls. (Mark 8:36-38)
                                            </p>
                                            <p>Why is the day of judgment an important matter to pause and consider?</p>
                                            <ol type="a">
                                                <li style="list-style: unset">
                                                    God is a holy and just God. For God to be true to who he is he
                                                    must uphold his law and punish sin. The bible tells us that if God
                                                    was to mark iniquity no one would stand (Psalm 130:3-4; Jeremiah
                                                    32:19; 1 Samuel 2:25)
                                                </li>
                                                <li style="list-style: unset">
                                                    We are all sinners and therefore Godâ€™s judgment hangs upon us
                                                    (Romans 3:10-18, 23). No one is righteous before God and to make the
                                                    matter worse even own righteous deeds are like filthy rags before
                                                    Him (Isaiah 64:6).
                                                </li>
                                                <li style="list-style: unset">
                                                    The wages of sin is death (Roams 6:23). The place of eternal
                                                    separation from God for unrepentant sinners is hell. It is one thing
                                                    to be rejected by family or friends but it is entirely a different
                                                    thing to be eternally separated in hell from God who is the source
                                                    of life, peace and happiness (Matthew 10:28; Revelation 21:8)
                                                </li>
                                            </ol>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="accordion-item">
                                    <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingOne">
                                        <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button"
                                            data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseOne"
                                            aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseOne">
                                            What then is the way forward?
                                        </button>
                                    </h2>
                                    <div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                                        aria-labelledby="headingOne" data-bs-parent="#accordionFaq">
                                        <div class="accordion-body">
                                            <ol type="a">
                                                <li style="list-style: unset">
                                                    God in his great mercy and grace gave up his son Jesus Christ to die
                                                    on the cross on our behalf. He died the death we should have died.
                                                    He suffered the punishment we should have suffered (John 3:16;
                                                    Galatians 3:13; 2 Cor 5:21; Romans 5:8; Ephesians 2:1-8)
                                                </li>
                                                <li style="list-style: unset">
                                                    God then commands us to repent and turn away from our sinful ways
                                                    and to trust that the death and blood of Jesus Christ and his
                                                    resurrection is sufficient to cleanse us and make us as white as
                                                    snow. (Mark 1:15)
                                                </li>
                                            </ol>
                                            <p>
                                                The only way to be ready for the judgment is to sincerely and humbly
                                                come to the Lord and confess to him how you have sinned against him,
                                                used him and mocked him and that you do not have what it takes to
                                                deliver yourself from his judgment nor do you have the holiness needed
                                                to stand before him. You must pray and plead with God to open your eyes
                                                to see your sinfulness and by his grace to cry him to save you from his
                                                wrath and to make you his child.
                                            </p>
                                            <p>There is no greater joy and peace than knowing that you are forgiven and
                                                accepted by God based on the life and work of Christ (Romans 5:1,8;
                                                8:1).
                                            </p>
                                            <p>If you need help in understanding these glorious truths please feel free
                                                to email or call us. In addition, if you are looking for a church that
                                                will teach you how to know Jesus, follow him and serve him please
                                                consider visiting us and we will be glad to welcome you.

                                            </p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
